    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nAfter running `test/functional/options/defaults_spec.lua`, some directories are left in the repo root. These are named `~`, `,=,=,` and `$VARIABLES`.\n\nWhen these directories are present, running `test/functional/vimscript/environ_spec.lua` will fail. This is caused by the presence of the `~` directory specifically.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\n$ TEST_FILE=test/functional/options/defaults_spec.lua make functionaltest\n$ ls # Note the extra directories\n$ TEST_FILE=test/functional/vimscript/environ_spec.lua make functionaltest\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo extra directories should be left behind after running `options/defaults_spec`. `vimscript/environ_spec` should run successfully.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nLatest master, 103ddaf9ae80a32e50325888b0cde1c4354f8413\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian Linux 13.2 (podman container)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nN/A\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nN/A\n\n### Installation\n\ngit",
